examples.en: He climbed stiffly out of the car.
The key turned stiffly in the lock.
The soldiers stood stiffly to attention.
That poor stiff never gets a break.
He sat stiffly, with a pained expression on his face.
She sat stiffly upright, feet together, hands in her lap.
When I got out of bed this morning my back was stiff as a board.
Beat the egg whites until they are stiff.
The cloth on the table was so stiffly starched that it stuck out at the corners.
They have the kind of luxuries the average working stiff can't afford.
